description: Almost no code comments unless they directly help agents; no narration
alwaysApply: true
---

# Minimal comments in code (scaffold)

- **Default:** no comment—let the code and names speak.
- **Allowed:** short comments that **steer an agent** (non-obvious invariant, “why not the obvious approach”, security footgun, link to a rule or pattern file).
- **Avoid:** restating what the next line does, “this variable is used for X and Y”, tutorial-style blocks, or repeating docstrings the types already express.
